from sklearn.gaussian_process import GaussianProcessRegressor

    f=objective_function,
    pbounds={'x': (0, 10)},
    random_state=1,
    verbose=2,
    allow_duplicate_points=True
)

import numpy as np
from scipy.stats import norm
def expected_improvement(x, x_samples, y_samples, best_y, acq_func):
    mu, sigma = acq_func(x)
    mu_samples = acq_func(x_samples)
    sigma_samples = np.abs(sigma)
    mu_improvement = mu - best_y
    z = (mu_samples - best_y - mu_improvement) / sigma_samples
    ei = mu_improvement * norm.cdf(z) + sigma_samples * norm.pdf(z)
    return np.max(ei)
